In a pestle and mortar blend together the peppercorns, garlic, ginger, orange zest, spring onions and chilli until you have a paste.In a large bowl combine the honey, soy sauce and oils with the paste.  Season to taste.  Add the chicken wings, turn to coat, then allow to marinate for at least 4 hours or preferably overnight.Cook the chicken wings in a hot griddle pan or on a hot barbecue for 7-8 minutes each side or until thoroughly cooked and golden brown.Garnish the chicken with a mixture of orange zest, chopped parsley and chives.